2.NodeJS http module
NodeJS http module
NodeJs http module is an integral component that facilitates various aspects of the HTTP protocol. To use the
http module, start by creating a new file named "server.js" and then im%ort the http module using the require()
function, as demonstrated in the following example:

const http=require('http');
const server=http.createServer((req,res)=>{
     if(req.url=='/'){
        res.write('<h1> HELLO NODE.Js </h1');
     }else if(req.url=='/about')
     {


     res.end();
})

server.listen(5000);
console.log('The http request is running on port 5000');


